##Calculating the factorial of a Number

#In mathematics, the notation n! represents the factorial of the nonnegativ
#int n. The factorial of n is the product of all the nonnegative integers from 1
#to n.

##Write a program that lets the user enter a nonnegative integer then uses a loop
#to calculate the  factorial of that number. Display the factorial

num = int(input("> "))
count = 0
list1 = []
suma = 0

for n in range(num):
    count += 1
    suma += count
    list1.append(count)
    list1.append("X")

del list1[-1]

print(num,"!=", *list1,"=",suma)
